# The async tests intentionally drive capturing lambda-coroutines. Such a lambda is normally a
# lifetime footgun (its closure is not copied into the coroutine frame), which is exactly what
# `cppcoreguidelines-avoid-capturing-lambda-coroutines` guards against. Here, however, every such
# coroutine is driven through RunPumped/RunBlocking (see AsyncTestUtils.hpp), which keep the
# closure alive for the whole run — a pattern clang-tidy cannot see. Disabling the two coroutine
# checks for the test sources keeps the tests readable; the library code under src/Lightweight
# keeps both checks fully enforced.
InheritParentConfig: true
Checks: >
  -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-capturing-lambda-coroutines,
  -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-reference-coroutine-parameters
